modules.description: This module handles cryptographic operations for secure software updates, including key generation, message signing, and signature verification. It works with base64-encoded public keys, secret keys, and signatures in the signify format. Concrete use cases include verifying downloaded artifacts, generating key pairs for release signing, and checking the integrity of software updates using embedded public keys and signed metadata.

This module implements cryptographic primitives for secure software updates, supporting key generation, signing, and signature verification using base64-encoded keys and signatures in the signify format. It enables verifying the integrity of downloaded artifacts, generating key pairs for release signing, and validating updates using embedded public keys and signed metadata. Key operations include signing data with a secret key, verifying signatures against a public key, and parsing or serializing keys and signatures in the expected format. Example use cases include securing dataset updates, authenticating software releases, and ensuring tamper-proof distribution of configuration files.
